				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{1}{16}$$\end{document}116 year−1 and a Q10 of 1.75.

Silicate weathering rates throughout the PETM are estimated considering the CESM climate inputs, the topographic reconstruction of ref. 84 and vegetation biomass estimates from the TREED vegetation model. We apply a weathering equation commonly used in deep-time biogeochemical models86,89:24\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
